const collection = dao.findCollectionByNameOrId("example")
const record = new Record(collection, {
"title": "example",
})
dao.saveRecord(record);
}, (db) => { // down
const dao = new Dao(db)
...
I see a bunch of js files **that were automatically created when I created a collection or made a change**.
All the changes are stored automatically as migrations files.
I copied those JS files into the pb_migrations directory, and then when I create a new docker container, the migrations happen automatically.
...
There are no typings for the JS migrations.
...
